# Root-level Docker build context exclusions. Without this, every
# `docker build .` uploads vendor/, node_modules, and .git — minutes
# of wasted I/O on every rebuild.
#
# The frontend/ subdir has its own .dockerignore that applies when
# `frontend/Dockerfile` is the build context (now legacy/unused), but
# it's NOT honored when this root Dockerfile copies frontend/ — Docker
# only consults the .dockerignore at the build context root.

# JS/TS build artifacts (rebuilt inside the dashboard-build stage)
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/out
**/dist
**/build
**/coverage

# PHP/Composer artifacts (the openemr base image ships its own copy of
# the application; we only inject specific files)
vendor

# Tests and fixtures (runtime image doesn't need them)
**/tests
**/*.test.ts
**/*.test.tsx
tests

# Env files (frontend reads env at runtime from Railway)
**/.env
**/.env.local
**/.env.*.local

# IDE / OS noise
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store
**/*.log

# Git metadata
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# Docker artifacts
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
frontend/Dockerfile
docker-compose*.yml
docker

# Claude / planning artifacts
.claude
memory-bank

# OpenEMR top-level dirs not needed by either build stage. The openemr
# runtime stage uses the upstream image's bundled copy of the application;
# we only inject specific files (copilot fragments + dashboard.php +
# proxy config + entrypoint).
Documentation
contrib
tests
ccdaservice
swagger
sql/databases
sql/sql_patch_*
